                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Fletcher reports that at a formal conference this afternoon at the foreign
                    office he was assured by Na-t’ung and Liang Tun-yen that the general principle
                    of the project referred to in department’s telegram of December 14 is approved
                    by the Chinese Government, and that he was also informed that further
                    consideration of the Chinchow project is necessary.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
